  |     R e l e a s e   N o t e s                                           |
  |   - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -   |
  |                                                                         |
  |   You play the game as Paul Prospero, an occult-minded detective who    |
  |   receives a disturbing letter from Ethan Carter. Realizing the boy     |
  |   is in grave danger, Paul arrives at Ethan's home of Red Creek         |
  |   Valley, where things turn out to be even worse than he imagined.      |
  |   Ethan has vanished in the wake of a brutal murder, which Paul         |
  |   quickly discerns might not be the only local murder worth looking     |
  |   into.                                                                 |
  |                                                                         |
  |   Inspired by the weird fiction and other tales of the macabre from     |
  |   the early twentieth century, The Vanishing of Ethan Carter aims to    |
  |   significantly evolve immersive storytelling in games. While it        |
  |   features a private detective and quite a few mental challenges, The   |
  |   Vanishing of Ethan Carter's focus is on atmosphere, mood, and the     |
  |   essential humanity of our characters.                                 |
  |                                                                         |
  |   Languages: English, French, Italian, German and Spanish.              |
